metadata.description:
The derivative collection of strokes.gmi.sh â€“Â the original, the first on-chain abstract art collection by gmi.sh. Each Stroke is defined on êœ© blockchain, the assets are stored on IPFS and rendered through fxhash contract.

metadata.name: B L I T Z E R S #43
metadata.description:
Created with math and p5js.
- 23 color palettes.
- random scales.
- random dimensions.

Use "S" key to save the image ( default quality )
In live mode, add &size="pixel_size" to change the pixel size of the image for export.( save image ) For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

Collectors have the right to print.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

Artwork by aretez
https://twitter.com/aretezos

metadata.name: Vers #227
metadata.description:
Vers

A flexibility in regards to position.

V : Switch the top to the bottom or vice versa
A : Toggle reveal animation/title card
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Beyond #280
metadata.description:
I have often looked at images from space and wished there were some way I could travel to the far off stars, galaxies, and nebulae, to see them with my own eyes. This project captures glimpses of these distant places. Come discover previously unseen reaches of the universe one mint at a time!

This project includes the following features: color palette, number of stars, total star layers, and number of nebulae.

metadata.name: Annum #8311
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Waveforms #9
metadata.description:
A set of waveforms - maybe audio snippets? maybe EEG traces? maybe a seismographic record of many small earthquakes.

Generated using a neural network (Variational Autoencoder) trained on a wide array of waveforms.

May need to click on the canvas to hear the sound.

A zigzag is a pattern made up of small corners at variable angles, though constant within the zigzag, tracing a path between two parallel lines; it can be described as both jagged and fairly regular.
In geometry, this pattern is described as a skew apeirogon. From the point of view of symmetry, a regular zigzag can be generated from a simple motif like a line segment by repeated application of a glide reflection.

Another name for the pattern is "Herringbone" FYI ğŸ¤“

There's a chance no lines are shown at all, this is intentional, as I love "bugs" ğŸª²

A zigzag is a pattern made up of small corners at variable angles, though constant within the zigzag, tracing a path between two parallel lines; it can be described as both jagged and fairly regular.
In geometry, this pattern is described as a skew apeirogon. From the point of view of symmetry, a regular zigzag can be generated from a simple motif like a line segment by repeated application of a glide reflection.

Another name for the pattern is "Herringbone" FYI ğŸ¤“

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #7067
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Tunnels #860
metadata.description:
"Tunnels" explores using generative backgrounds to lead a field of isometric shapes. How the foreground and background interact varies wildly from generation to generation. "Tunnels" can seem to have an exit and sometimes seem to lead into nowhere.

Royalties Splits:
50% Donation to minter

Features:
Four different sizes: 9x16, 11x14", 12x18", 12x12"
Portrait or landscape orientation
~500 color pallets, one black and white, one cyan, magenta, yellow and black, and the rest from Jam3/nice-color-palettes.

A zigzag is a pattern made up of small corners at variable angles, though constant within the zigzag, tracing a path between two parallel lines; it can be described as both jagged and fairly regular.
In geometry, this pattern is described as a skew apeirogon. From the point of view of symmetry, a regular zigzag can be generated from a simple motif like a line segment by repeated application of a glide reflection.

Another name for the pattern is "Herringbone" FYI ğŸ¤“

There's a chance no lines are shown at all, this is intentional, as I love "bugs" ğŸª²
